            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#AA">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>pro felicitate dominorum
                    <lb n="2"/>Augustorumque <g ref="symbols.xml#ivy-leaf">❦</g>
                    <lb n="3"/><g ref="symbols.xml#ivy-leaf">❦</g> nostrorum <!-- palma -->
                    <lb n="4"/>ripam a parte sinisstra macelli
                    <lb n="5"/>iactis molibus propter incursione
                    <lb n="6"/>ingruentium procellarum
                    <lb n="7"/><persName type="attested"><name>Valerius</name> <name>Hermonius</name> <name>Maximus</name></persName> <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ir</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimus</ex></expan>
                    <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>cons</abbr><ex>ularis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Camp</abbr><ex>aniae</ex></expan> incoavit adque perfecit <g ref="symbols.xml#ivy-leaf">❦</g>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text from EDR, with comparison to photograph</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>For the prosperity of our masters and our Augusti, the riverbank on the left side of the market, with embarkments having been thrown up because of the onrush of violent storms. Valerius Hermonius Maximus, most illustrious man, consular of Campania, began and completed (the work). </p> <!-- Check transl. -->
